abstract: The president described negotiations between Washington and Beijing in positive terms but said, “Without the tariffs, we wouldn’t be talking.”

headline_main: Jail or Bail? There’s a New Option
headline_print_headline: Bail or Jail? There’s Another Option

abstract: Mr. Schultz, the former chief executive of Starbucks, was greeted by about 40 protesters at an event after saying he would consider running for president as an independent.
snippet: Mr. Schultz, the former chief executive of Starbucks, was greeted by about 40 protesters at an event after saying he would consider running for president as an independent.
lead_paragraph: SEATTLE — As cars and pedestrians passed by during the evening rush on Thursday, Paula Harper-Christensen, a retired teacher, smiled and waved her sign with an upside-down Starbucks mermaid. “Don’t spill our chance,” the text said under the logo. Susan Glicksberg’s protest placard was more blunt: “Do Not Run!”

headline_main: Howard Schultz Draws Protesters in His Hometown, Seattle

abstract: Of obsessions, vanity and delusions of superiority.
snippet: Of obsessions, vanity and delusions of superiority.
lead_paragraph: Why is American politics so dysfunctional? Whatever the deeper roots of our distress, the proximate cause is ideological extremism: Powerful factions are committed to false views of the world, regardless of the evidence.

abstract: In the On Politics newsletter: Ms. Abrams will be the first black woman to deliver the Democratic response to a State of the Union address.
snippet: In the On Politics newsletter: Ms. Abrams will be the first black woman to deliver the Democratic response to a State of the Union address.
lead_paragraph: Hi. Welcome to On Politics, your guide to the day in national politics. I’m Lisa Lerer, your host.

abstract: Facebook and Twitter said on Thursday that disinformation on their platforms now comes from more domestic and foreign sources — and not just Russia.
snippet: Facebook and Twitter said on Thursday that disinformation on their platforms now comes from more domestic and foreign sources — and not just Russia.
lead_paragraph: Russia created a playbook for spreading disinformation on social media. Now the rest of the world is following it.
